</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="CE4936C8FFAB7446FF07FB5AFEDDFAF3" blockId="21.[151,1025,1233,1295]" box="[151,367,1269,1295]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Urubamba Antpitta</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="86EC6543FFAB7446FF07FA99FBFEFAAC" box="[151,1100,1334,1360]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" type="description">
<paragraph id="CE4936C8FFAB7446FF07FA99FBFEFAAC" blockId="21.[151,1437,1334,2041]" box="[151,1100,1334,1360]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
Includes populations designated 
<emphasis id="FC82EADAFFAB7446FD95FA99FD04FAAC" box="[517,694,1334,1360]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
<taxonomicName id="09F64D4BFFAB7446FD95FA99FD21FAAC" baseAuthorityName="Chapman" baseAuthorityYear="1923" box="[517,659,1334,1360]" class="Aves" family="Grallariidae" genus="Grallaria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="occabambae">occabambae</taxonomicName>
1a
</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis id="FC82EADAFFAB7446FD7CFA99FC2FFAAC" box="[748,925,1334,1360]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
<taxonomicName id="09F64D4BFFAB7446FD7CFA99FCC8FAAC" baseAuthorityName="Chapman" baseAuthorityYear="1923" box="[748,890,1334,1360]" class="Aves" family="Grallariidae" genus="Grallaria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="occabambae">occabambae</taxonomicName>
1b
</emphasis>
in the analysis.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="86EC6543FFAB7446FF57FAF5FD0AF944" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="CE4936C8FFAB7446FF57FAF5FD0AF944" blockId="21.[151,1437,1334,2041]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
<emphasis id="FC82EADAFFAB7446FF57FAF5FEF0FA88" bold="true" box="[199,322,1370,1396]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Nominate form upperparts dark reddish yellow-brown; underparts lighter with pale feather edgings; undertail coverts pale yellowish-buff. Short songs of two (
<emphasis id="FC82EADAFFAB7446FCA3FAD0FBB0FA64" box="[819,1026,1406,1433]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
G. o. 
<taxonomicName id="09F64D4BFFAB7446FCE4FAD1FBB0FA64" baseAuthorityName="Chapman" baseAuthorityYear="1923" box="[884,1026,1406,1432]" class="Aves" family="Grallariidae" genus="Grallaria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="occabambae">occabambae</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
) (
<figureCitation id="56CD2A4DFFAB7446FB8CFAD1FBC2FA65" box="[1052,1136,1406,1433]" captionStart="FIGURE 15" captionStartId="22.[151,250,551,575]" captionTargetBox="[168,1420,185,520]" captionTargetId="figure@22.[164,1422,181,525]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="FIGURE 15. Songs of Grallaria o. occabambae: (A) long song, Carrizales, Cusco, Peru (Lane ML236893); (B) short song, San Luis, Cusco (Krabbe XC47645)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3954729" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3954729/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Fig. 15</figureCitation>
) or three (
<taxonomicName id="09F64D4BFFAB7446FB7BFAD0FE8BFA40" authorityName=", Isler &amp; Chesser" authorityYear="2020" class="Aves" family="Grallariidae" genus="Grallaria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Chordata" rank="subSpecies" species="occabambae" subSpecies="marcapatensis">
<emphasis id="FC82EADAFFAB7446FB7BFAD0FE8BFA40" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">G. occabambae marcapatensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) (
<figureCitation id="56CD2A4DFFAB7446FEC5FA0DFE1BFA41" box="[341,425,1442,1469]" captionStart="FIGURE 16" captionStartId="22.[151,250,997,1021]" captionTargetBox="[168,1421,635,969]" captionTargetId="figure@22.[164,1424,633,971]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="FIGURE 16. Songs of Grallaria occabambae marcapatensis: (A) long song, Abra Acjanaco, Cusco, Peru (Lane ML236892); (B) short song, upper Manu Road, Cusco (Lane ML236891)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3954731" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3954731/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Fig. 16</figureCitation>
) unmodulated notes distinguish 
<taxonomicName id="09F64D4BFFAB7446FCB2FA0CFC67FA40" baseAuthorityName="Chapman" baseAuthorityYear="1923" box="[802,981,1442,1469]" class="Aves" family="Grallariidae" genus="Grallaria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="occabambae">
<emphasis id="FC82EADAFFAB7446FCB2FA0CFC67FA40" box="[802,981,1442,1469]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">G. occabambae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from all but the two-noted short songs of 
<taxonomicName id="09F64D4BFFAB7446FF28FA68FECAFA1C" authorityName="Bond &amp; Meyer de Schauensee" authorityYear="1940" box="[184,376,1478,1505]" class="Aves" family="Grallariidae" genus="Grallaria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="cochabambae">
<emphasis id="FC82EADAFFAB7446FF28FA68FECAFA1C" box="[184,376,1478,1505]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">G. cochabambae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="09F64D4BFFAB7446FE22FA68FD8CFA1C" authorityName="Robbins, Isler, Chesser, &amp; Tobias" authorityYear="2020" box="[434,574,1479,1505]" class="Aves" family="Grallariidae" genus="Grallaria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="sinaensis">
<emphasis id="FC82EADAFFAB7446FE22FA68FD8CFA1C" box="[434,574,1479,1505]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">G. sinaensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Short song notes of 
<taxonomicName id="09F64D4BFFAB7446FCA6FA68FC5BFA1C" baseAuthorityName="Chapman" baseAuthorityYear="1923" box="[822,1001,1478,1505]" class="Aves" family="Grallariidae" genus="Grallaria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="occabambae">
<emphasis id="FC82EADAFFAB7446FCA6FA68FC5BFA1C" box="[822,1001,1478,1505]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">G. occabambae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differ from those of 
<taxonomicName id="09F64D4BFFAB7446FB4CFA68FA2FFA1C" authorityName="Bond &amp; Meyer de Schauensee" authorityYear="1940" box="[1244,1437,1478,1505]" class="Aves" family="Grallariidae" genus="Grallaria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="cochabambae">
<emphasis id="FC82EADAFFAB7446FB4CFA68FA2FFA1C" box="[1244,1437,1478,1505]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">G. cochabambae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="09F64D4BFFAB7446FF57FA44FEE0F9F8" authorityName="Robbins, Isler, Chesser, &amp; Tobias" authorityYear="2020" box="[199,338,1515,1541]" class="Aves" family="Grallariidae" genus="Grallaria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="sinaensis">
<emphasis id="FC82EADAFFAB7446FF57FA44FEE0F9F8" box="[199,338,1515,1541]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">G. sinaensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in being rounded (as opposed to flat and slightly downslurred) and by longer notes and internote intervals. Long songs of 
<taxonomicName id="09F64D4BFFAB7446FE3EF9A0FDEDF9D4" baseAuthorityName="Chapman" baseAuthorityYear="1923" box="[430,607,1550,1577]" class="Aves" family="Grallariidae" genus="Grallaria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="occabambae">
<emphasis id="FC82EADAFFAB7446FE3EF9A0FDEDF9D4" box="[430,607,1550,1577]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">G. occabambae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differ from those of 
<taxonomicName id="09F64D4BFFAB7446FCDAF9A0FBBAF9D4" authorityName="Bond &amp; Meyer de Schauensee" authorityYear="1940" box="[842,1032,1550,1577]" class="Aves" family="Grallariidae" genus="Grallaria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="cochabambae">
<emphasis id="FC82EADAFFAB7446FCDAF9A0FBBAF9D4" box="[842,1032,1550,1577]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">G. cochabambae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="09F64D4BFFAB7446FBAFF9A0FB7BF9D4" authorityName="Robbins, Isler, Chesser, &amp; Tobias" authorityYear="2020" box="[1087,1225,1551,1577]" class="Aves" family="Grallariidae" genus="Grallaria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="sinaensis">
<emphasis id="FC82EADAFFAB7446FBAFF9A0FB7BF9D4" box="[1087,1225,1551,1577]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">G. sinaensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in having inverted U-shaped notes (as opposed to flat or downslurred notes), in having internote intervals lengthening (as opposed to lengthening, stabilizing, and shortening) resulting in decelerating pace, and in having a flat or slowly declining peak frequency pattern (as opposed to peaks decreasing, stabilizing, and increasing); also apparently in overall pace, although small sample sizes limit diagnosability.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="86EC6543FFAB7446FF57F96DFDD6F805" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="CE4936C8FFAB7446FF57F96DFBBBF8D8" blockId="21.[151,1437,1334,2041]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
<emphasis id="FC82EADAFFAB7446FF57F96DFED3F920" bold="true" box="[199,353,1730,1756]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Distribution.</emphasis>
Endemic to 
<collectingCountry id="B6E17658FFAB7446FE7CF96CFDADF921" box="[492,543,1731,1757]" name="Peru" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Peru</collectingCountry>
in extreme eastern 
<collectingRegion id="0C32F82AFFAB7446FD67F96DFC86F920" box="[759,820,1730,1756]" country="Peru" name="Junin" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Junín</collectingRegion>
(Cordillera Vilcabamba) and 
<collectingRegion id="0C32F82AFFAB7446FBEEF96CFB76F921" box="[1150,1220,1731,1757]" country="Peru" name="Cusco" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Cusco</collectingRegion>
east of the Río Ene and Río 
<collectingRegion id="0C32F82AFFAB7446FF64F949FED6F8FC" box="[244,356,1766,1792]" country="Peru" name="Apurimac" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Apurímac</collectingRegion>
and between the Río Tambo to the north and the Río Marcapata to the south, 
<quantity id="090E9B2DFFAB7446FB53F949FAD3F8FD" box="[1219,1377,1766,1793]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.05" metricValueMax="3.65" metricValueMin="2.45" pageId="21" pageNumber="22" unit="m" value="3050.0" valueMax="3650.0" valueMin="2450.0">2450–3650 m</quantity>
. Two subspecies; nominate subspecies occurs west of the Río Yanatili valley, 
<collectingRegion id="0C32F82AFFAB7446FC2BF8A5FBB7F8D8" box="[955,1029,1802,1828]" country="Peru" name="Cusco" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Cusco</collectingRegion>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="CE4936C8FFAB7446FF57F881FDD6F805" blockId="21.[151,1437,1334,2041]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">
<emphasis id="FC82EADAFFAB7446FF57F881FE85F8B4" bold="true" box="[199,311,1838,1864]" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">Plumage.</emphasis>
Overall plumage of upperparts, including rectrices, remiges (primaries edged paler), crown and auriculars, typically dark reddish-yellow-brown (7.5YR 4/4) but variable, tending toward browner (5YR 4/4) in nominate form and lighter and brighter (7.5YR 5/6) in 
<emphasis id="FC82EADAFFAB7446FD49F8DAFC0CF872" box="[729,958,1909,1935]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">G. o. marcapatensis</emphasis>
; malar tending to color of breast. Throat, breast and belly light reddish yellow-brown (7.5YR 6/8) with pale feather edgings. Undertail coverts pale yellowish-buff (2.5Y 8/4) in nominate form and light reddish-yellow-brown (7.5YR 7/8) in 
<emphasis id="FC82EADAFFAB7446FBD4F813FA91F829" box="[1092,1315,1980,2006]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="22">G. o. marcapatensis</emphasis>
(specimen photographs App. 6, Figs. A29 and A30).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<caption id="9A896640FFA87445FF07FD88FE50FD9F" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3954729" ID-Zenodo-Dep="3954729" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3954729/files/figure.png" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" startId="22.[151,250,551,575]" targetBox="[168,1420,185,520]" targetPageId="22">
<paragraph id="CE4936C8FFA87445FF07FD88FE50FD9F" blockId="22.[151,1436,551,611]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">
<emphasis id="FC82EADAFFA87445FF07FD88FEAAFDC3" bold="true" box="[151,280,551,575]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">FIGURE 15</emphasis>
. Songs of 
<emphasis id="FC82EADAFFA87445FE12FD88FD33FDC3" box="[386,641,551,575]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">
<taxonomicName id="09F64D4BFFA87445FE12FD88FE51FDC3" authorityName="Vieillot" authorityYear="1816" box="[386,483,551,575]" class="Aves" family="Grallariidae" genus="Grallaria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Grallaria</taxonomicName>
o. 
<taxonomicName id="09F64D4BFFA87445FD91FD88FD33FDC3" baseAuthorityName="Chapman" baseAuthorityYear="1923" box="[513,641,551,575]" class="Aves" family="Grallariidae" genus="Grallaria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="occabambae">occabambae</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
: (A) long song, Carrizales, Cusco, Peru (Lane ML236893); (B) short song, San Luis, Cusco (Krabbe XC47645).
</paragraph>
</caption>
<caption id="9A896640FFA87445FF07FC4AFCB3FBDD" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3954731" ID-Zenodo-Dep="3954731" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3954731/files/figure.png" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" startId="22.[151,250,997,1021]" targetBox="[168,1421,635,969]" targetPageId="22">
