<subSubSection id="86EC6543FFA87445FF57FBFFFC49FB95" box="[199,1019,1103,1130]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="CE4936C8FFA87445FF57FBFFFC49FB95" blockId="22.[151,1437,1103,1487]" box="[199,1019,1103,1130]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">
<emphasis id="FC82EADAFFA87445FF57FBFFFEFCFB96" bold="true" box="[199,334,1104,1130]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Etymology.</emphasis>
The English name is adapted from 
<bibRefCitation id="AA674B39FFA87445FD4DFBE0FC45FB95" author="Cory, C. B. &amp; Hellmayr, C. E." box="[733,1015,1103,1129]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" pagination="1 - 369" refId="ref21765" refString="Cory, C. B. &amp; Hellmayr, C. E. (1924) Catalogue of birds of the Americas and the adjacent islands. Pteroptochidae-Conopophagidae-Formicariidae. Field Museum of Natural History, Zoological Series, No. 13, Part 3, 1 - 369." type="book chapter" year="1924">Cory &amp; Hellmayr (1924)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="86EC6543FFA87445FF57FBDCFC4CFA33" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="CE4936C8FFA87445FF57FBDCFC4CFA33" blockId="22.[151,1437,1103,1487]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">
<emphasis id="FC82EADAFFA87445FF57FBDCFE89FB71" bold="true" box="[199,315,1139,1165]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Remarks.</emphasis>
The distinction in number of notes in short songs indicates that 
<emphasis id="FC82EADAFFA87445FB96FBDCFB05FB71" box="[1030,1207,1139,1165]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">
<taxonomicName id="09F64D4BFFA87445FB96FBDCFB26FB71" baseAuthorityName="Chapman" baseAuthorityYear="1923" box="[1030,1172,1139,1165]" class="Aves" family="Grallariidae" genus="Grallaria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="occabambae">occabambae</taxonomicName>
1a
</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis id="FC82EADAFFA87445FB7CFBDCFA2FFB71" box="[1260,1437,1139,1165]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">
<taxonomicName id="09F64D4BFFA87445FB7CFBDCFAC8FB71" baseAuthorityName="Chapman" baseAuthorityYear="1923" box="[1260,1402,1139,1165]" class="Aves" family="Grallariidae" genus="Grallaria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="occabambae">occabambae</taxonomicName>
1b
</emphasis>
should be considered subspecifically distinct, and a new subspecies is described below. Compared to neighboring taxa, plumage of 
<taxonomicName id="09F64D4BFFA87445FECDFB15FDBCFB2F" baseAuthorityName="Chapman" baseAuthorityYear="1923" box="[349,526,1209,1236]" class="Aves" family="Grallariidae" genus="Grallaria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="occabambae">
<emphasis id="FC82EADAFFA87445FECDFB15FDBCFB2F" box="[349,526,1209,1236]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">G. occabambae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is paler and separable from that of 
<taxonomicName id="09F64D4BFFA87445FC33FB16FBCAFB2F" authorityName="Hosner, Robbins, Isler, &amp; Chesser" authorityYear="2020" box="[931,1144,1209,1235]" class="Aves" family="Grallariidae" genus="Grallaria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="centralis">
<emphasis id="FC82EADAFFA87445FC33FB16FBCAFB2F" box="[931,1144,1209,1235]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">Grallaria centralis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="09F64D4BFFA87445FB21FB15FADBFB2F" authorityName="Hosner, Robbins, Isler, &amp; Chesser" authorityYear="2020" box="[1201,1385,1209,1236]" class="Aves" family="Grallariidae" genus="Grallaria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="ayacuchensis">
<emphasis id="FC82EADAFFA87445FB21FB15FADBFB2F" box="[1201,1385,1209,1236]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">G. ayacuchensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but similarly colored 
<taxonomicName id="09F64D4BFFA87445FECDFB72FE60FB0B" authorityName="Isler, Chesser, Robbins &amp; Hosner" authorityYear="2020" box="[349,466,1245,1271]" class="Aves" family="Grallariidae" genus="Grallaria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="gravesi">
<emphasis id="FC82EADAFFA87445FECDFB72FE60FB0B" box="[349,466,1245,1271]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">G. gravesi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="09F64D4BFFA87445FE71FB72FDEFFB0B" authorityName="Berlepsch &amp; Stolzmann" authorityYear="1896" box="[481,605,1245,1271]" class="Aves" family="Grallariidae" genus="Grallaria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="obscura">
<emphasis id="FC82EADAFFA87445FE71FB72FDEFFB0B" box="[481,605,1245,1271]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">G. obscura</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="09F64D4BFFA87445FD04FB72FCACFB0B" authorityName="Robbins, Isler, Chesser, &amp; Tobias" authorityYear="2020" box="[660,798,1245,1271]" class="Aves" family="Grallariidae" genus="Grallaria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="sinaensis">
<emphasis id="FC82EADAFFA87445FD04FB72FCACFB0B" box="[660,798,1245,1271]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">G. sinaensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
appear to be distinguished from 
<taxonomicName id="09F64D4BFFA87445FB00FB72FAF2FB0B" baseAuthorityName="Chapman" baseAuthorityYear="1923" box="[1168,1344,1245,1271]" class="Aves" family="Grallariidae" genus="Grallaria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="occabambae">
<emphasis id="FC82EADAFFA87445FB00FB72FAF2FB0B" box="[1168,1344,1245,1271]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">G. occabambae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
only by the greater extent of pale edgings on the breast feathers of 
<taxonomicName id="09F64D4BFFA87445FCA9FAAEFC5BFAE6" baseAuthorityName="Chapman" baseAuthorityYear="1923" box="[825,1001,1280,1307]" class="Aves" family="Grallariidae" genus="Grallaria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="occabambae">
<emphasis id="FC82EADAFFA87445FCA9FAAEFC5BFAE6" box="[825,1001,1280,1307]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">G. occabambae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, a character requiring confirmation in large samples. Nominate form includes 
<emphasis id="FC82EADAFFA87445FDC9FA8BFCB9FAC3" box="[601,779,1316,1343]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">
<taxonomicName id="09F64D4BFFA87445FDC9FA8BFD55FAC2" baseAuthorityName="Chapman" baseAuthorityYear="1923" box="[601,743,1316,1342]" class="Aves" family="Grallariidae" genus="Grallaria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="occabambae">occabambae</taxonomicName>
1a
</emphasis>
. It appears that the Río Yanatili valley separates ranges of subspecies of 
<taxonomicName id="09F64D4BFFA87445FEA5FAE6FE54FA9E" baseAuthorityName="Chapman" baseAuthorityYear="1923" box="[309,486,1352,1379]" class="Aves" family="Grallariidae" genus="Grallaria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="occabambae">
<emphasis id="FC82EADAFFA87445FEA5FAE6FEFBFA9F" box="[309,329,1353,1379]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">G</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="FC82EADAFFA87445FEC8FAE7FE54FA9E" box="[344,486,1352,1378]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">occabambae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The phylogeny (
<bibRefCitation id="AA674B39FFA87445FD3CFAE7FC3BFA9F" author="Chesser, R. T. &amp; Isler, M. L. &amp; Cuervo, A. M. &amp; Cadena, C. D. &amp; Galen, S. C. &amp; Bergner, L. M. &amp; Fleischer, R. C. &amp; Bravo, G. A. &amp; Lane, D. F. &amp; Hosner, P. A." box="[684,905,1352,1379]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" pagination="1 - 25" refId="ref21648" refString="Chesser, R. T., Isler, M. L., Cuervo, A. M., Cadena, C. D., Galen, S. C., Bergner, L. M., Fleischer, R. C., Bravo, G. A., Lane, D. F. &amp; Hosner, P. A. (2020) Conservative plumage masks extraordinary genetic diversity in the Grallaria rufula (Rufous Antpitta) complex of the humid Andes. The Auk: Ornithological Advances, 137, 1 - 25. https: // doi. org / 10.1093 / auk / ukaa 009" type="journal article" year="2020">
Chesser 
<emphasis id="FC82EADAFFA87445FC9EFAE6FCF5FA9E" box="[782,839,1352,1378]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">et al.</emphasis>
2020
</bibRefCitation>
) includes in 
<emphasis id="FC82EADAFFA87445FB8AFAE7FB79FA9E" box="[1050,1227,1352,1378]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">
<taxonomicName id="09F64D4BFFA87445FB8AFAE7FB1AFA9E" baseAuthorityName="Chapman" baseAuthorityYear="1923" box="[1050,1192,1352,1378]" class="Aves" family="Grallariidae" genus="Grallaria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="occabambae">occabambae</taxonomicName>
1b
</emphasis>
a specimen (MSB 168436) collected on a mountain bordering the Río Yanatili to the east, and the 
<typeStatus id="114D886AFFA87445FB80FAC2FBF2FA7B" box="[1040,1088,1389,1415]" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">type</typeStatus>
locality of 
<taxonomicName id="09F64D4BFFA87445FB50FAC2FF0DFA56" baseAuthorityName="Chapman" baseAuthorityYear="1923" class="Aves" family="Grallariidae" genus="Grallaria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Chordata" rank="subSpecies" species="rufula" subSpecies="occabambae">
<emphasis id="FC82EADAFFA87445FB50FAC2FB66FA7B" box="[1216,1236,1389,1415]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">G</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="FC82EADAFFA87445FB72FAC3FF0DFA56" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">rufula occabambae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is the Occabamba Valley = Río Ocobamba, which is a western tributary of the Río Yanatili (
<bibRefCitation id="AA674B39FFA87445FB50FA3FFF61FA33" author="Stephens, L. &amp; Traylor, M. A. Jr." pageId="22" pageNumber="23" refId="ref23932" refString="Stephens, L. &amp; Traylor, M. A. Jr. (1983) Ornithological gazetteer of Peru. Museum of Comparative Zoology, Cambridge, Massachusetts, 271 pp." type="book" year="1983">Stephens &amp; Traylor 1983</bibRefCitation>
). Recordings from the upper reaches of this river are of 
<emphasis id="FC82EADAFFA87445FCD6FA1BFC45FA33" box="[838,1015,1460,1487]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="23">
<taxonomicName id="09F64D4BFFA87445FCD6FA1BFC66FA32" baseAuthorityName="Chapman" baseAuthorityYear="1923" box="[838,980,1460,1486]" class="Aves" family="Grallariidae" genus="Grallaria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Passeriformes" pageId="22" pageNumber="23" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="occabambae">occabambae</taxonomicName>
1a
</emphasis>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
